undoubtedly its emergence from colonial rule on 27 April 1960. On that day, Togolese became fully sovereign. However, independence did not bring an end to oppression, as Gyasi translates from Paa Joe’s own words:

‘A year after independence, we were already under a military regime. Independence did not bring much because they [Franco-German origin Togo] were still there. They were the dictators.’

Gyasi has captured an important part of our history in what I consider to be his best work of art in this monumental exhibition.
